# UI Component Rules

## shadcn/ui Components

This project uses shadcn/ui (Radix UI + Tailwind). Available primitives in `src/components/ui/`:

alert, avatar, badge, button, card, checkbox, collapsible, command, dialog, drawer, input, label, multi-select, popover, radio-group, scroll-area, select, separator, sheet, slider, textarea, tooltip

When building UI, compose from these existing primitives before creating custom ones.

## Component Structure

```tsx
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from "react"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

// 2. Types
interface FeatureCardProps {
  title: string
  onAction: () => void
  children: React.ReactNode
}

// 3. Component
export function FeatureCard({ title, onAction, children }: FeatureCardProps) {
  const [isExpanded, setIsExpanded] = useState(false)

  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>{title}</CardHeader>
      <CardContent>{children}</CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

## Patterns

- Use `Drawer` (vaul) for bottom sheets on mobile (this is a mobile-first app)
- Use `Dialog` for confirmation/alert modals
- Use `Swiper` for image carousels (profile media gallery)
- Use `Sheet` for side panels
- Navigation via `ContentNavigation` with bottom nav bar

## Responsive Design

- This is a **Telegram Mini-App** — design for mobile viewport first
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes only when desktop layout differs
- Touch-friendly tap targets (min 44px)
- Respect safe areas for Telegram webview
